  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This spell lets you convince a beast that you mean it no harm. Choose a beast that you can see within range. It must see and hear you. If the beast's Intelligence is 4 or higher, the spell fails. Otherwise, the beast must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be charmed by you for the spell's duration. If you or one of your companions harms the target, the spell ends.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can affect one additional beast for each slot level above 1st.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>FoundryVTT:Â </strong> Checks for creature type and intelligence are not automated.</p>",
